column71: Charging for alerts to abnormal conditions, when especially in the chronically ill a spike in heart rate or a fall may be life-threatening, is deeply immoral. While the free app functions may be beneficial, I would choose to not to buy into a service that is predatory on nature. There is not currently an affordable monitor like this, and the potential is very exciting. The idea of having to pay in order to take it from "novelty self-study" to "medically useful" is abhorrent.
